OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FStop caging people with    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fautism and learning        
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fdisabilities, says Robert  
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Ex-Justice Secretary Sir Robert        
OL,6, Buckland is calling for changes to     
OL,7, mental health laws to stop people with 
OL,8, autism or learning disabilities being  
OL,9, detained in hospitals for long periods.
OL,11,FLast year, the BBC found that 100      
OL,12,Fpeople with learning disabilities and  
OL,13,Fautism had been held in hospitals for  
OL,14,Fat least 20 years.                     
OL,16,FSir Robert said the "effective caging  
OL,17,Fof human beings" was "out of date".    
OL,19,FThe government said it was "determined"
OL,20,Fto reduce numbers in hospitals.        
